stylometry: You want to have enough inventory so that you have it when you need it, but are not spending money holding it.  As a business, you always need to have the proper inventory in stock.  If you have not produced it, you will not have it.  However, if you produce too much of it, you will have to pay costs for keeping it in a warehouse.  The dilemma comes down to you figuring out how quickly you use you inventory so that you can order more to stock, but not producing it too far ahead so that it drives up storage costs.
